article.description: Amber Harris had 18 points to lead Xavier (No. 14 ESPN/USA Today, No. 12 AP) to an 81-60 victory over Mississippi State.
article.headline: Xavier routs Mississippi State after back-to-back losses
article.linkText: Late first-half run lets No. 14 Xavier snap skid
article.story:
CINCINNATI -- Amber Harris had 18 points to lead Xavier (No. 14 ESPN/USA Today, No. 12 AP) to an 81-60 victory over Mississippi State.

The Musketeers (8-2) were coming off back-to-back losses to Michigan State and Michigan. Xavier used a late first-half run to take control Sunday.

April Phillips added 16 points and Ta'Shia Phillips had her sixth double-double with 14 points and 13 rebounds. Harris also had six rebounds, helping Xavier dominate the boards 43-25.

Mary Kathryn Govero had 15 points for Mississippi State (8-4). Tysheka Grimes and Alexis Rack added 13 apiece.

Xavier went on an 18-5 run at the end of the first half for a 41-31 lead. The Musketeers scored the first seven points in the second half and were never in trouble again. The Musketeers shot 49 percent from the field and went 20 of 22 on free throws.
